HEADWORD: Holland
<hw>Hol"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of linen first
manufactured in Holland; a linen fabric used for window shades,
children's garments, etc.; <as>as, brown or unbleached
<ex>hollands</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

